<topic id='business_definition_accident_and_emergency_attendance_conclusion_time.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Accident and Emergency Attendance Conclusion Time - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>

  <p>
An 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_accident_and_emergency_attendance_conclusion_time">Accident and Emergency Attendance Conclusion Time</xref>
 is an 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_activity_date_time">ACTIVITY DATE TIME</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
An 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_accident_and_emergency_attendance_conclusion_time">Accident and Emergency Attendance Conclusion Time</xref>
 is the time, recorded using a 24 hour clock:  </p>
  <ul>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>
that a 
                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
's 
                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                     keyref="business_definition_accident_and_emergency_attendance">Accident and Emergency Attendance</xref>
 concludes or        </p>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>
when treatment in an 
                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                     keyref="business_definition_accident_and_emergency_department">Accident and Emergency Department</xref>
 is completed (whichever is the later).        </p>
         </div>
      </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
For those 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENTS</xref>
 admitted into hospital, the 
    <xref outputclass="element"
            keyref="element_a_and_e_attendance_conclusion_time">A and E ATTENDANCE CONCLUSION TIME</xref>
 is recorded as the time when the 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_decision_to_admit">DECISION TO ADMIT</xref>
 was made.  </p>

</body>
